.TH "mipi_dbi_poweron_conditional_reset" 9 "mipi_dbi_poweron_conditional_reset" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mipi_dbi_poweron_conditional_reset \- MIPI DBI poweron and conditional reset
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" mipi_dbi_poweron_conditional_reset
.BI "(struct mipi_dbi_dev *dbidev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dbidev" 12
MIPI DBI device structure
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function enables the regulator if used and if the display is off, it
does a hardware and software reset. If \fBmipi_dbi_display_is_on\fP determines
that the display is on, no reset is performed.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero if the controller was reset, 1 if the display was already on, or a
negative error code.
